From 1d562c8b552d869556b668fce7728939d4d55b1c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lutong <lutong14@huawei.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 22:37:53 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] mm/hugetlb: add fault-time reclaim, inactive list and
 NUMA policy

Implement fault-time direct reclaim for HugeTLB pages when OOM,
avoiding costly global reclaim. Add an inactive list with a
three-state machine and proactive reclaim to speed up fault-time
reclaim. Honour shared NUMA memory policy on hugetlbfs mappings
and fix lock ordering.

Signed-off-by: nashzhou <zhouhaipeng13@huawei.com>
---
 fs/hugetlbfs/inode.c    |   8 +-
 include/linux/hugetlb.h |  36 +++
 mm/hugetlb.c            | 549 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 mm/swap.c               |   7 +
 4 files changed, 572 insertions(+), 28 deletions(-)

